 2. Shared Backend: Database, API, and Services

 2.1 Key Database Entities (High-Level)
Only core tables; full schema detailed in relevant sections.

- users (id, email, phone, password_hash, role, created_at, …) – unified login for all portals.
- customers (user_id, first_name, last_name, default_address_id, wallet_balance)
- vendors (user_id, business_name, kyc_status, commission_rule, withdrawal_balance)
- addresses (id, user_id, label, street, city_id, lat, lon, is_default)
- cities (id, name, state, country_id)
- countries (id, code, name, currency, default_language)
- warehouses (id, name, city_id, type: ‘FC’ | ‘HUB’)
- products (id, vendor_id, name, description, brand_id, category_id, status)
- sku_variations (id, product_id, sku, barcode, weight_kg, dimensions_json, price, sale_price, low_stock_threshold)
- product_inventory (warehouse_id, sku_variation_id, available_qty, reserved_qty)
- orders (id, customer_id, total_amount, shipping_fee, status, payment_status, delivery_address_id, created_at)
- order_items (order_id, sku_variation_id, quantity, unit_price, fulfillment_type)
- vendor_orders (id, order_id, vendor_id, status, accept_deadline, ship_deadline, accept_timestamp, ship_timestamp)
- payment_transactions (id, order_id, gateway, reference, amount, status)
- escrow_ledger (id, transaction_id, order_id, buyer_id, amount, entry_type, status)
- commission_rules (category_id, country_id, type, value, effective_from)

 2.2 Shared APIs & Services
All portals communicate through a central REST API (with WebSocket for real-time updates). Key services:
- User Service: Auth, JWT issuing, OTP.
- Catalog Service: Products, categories, SKUs, search.
- Inventory Service: Stock levels, reservations, low-stock alerts.
- Order Service: Order state machine, order management.
- Fulfillment Service: Vendor order assignment, SLA tracking, shipment handling.
- Payment Service: Payment initialization, webhook processing, refunds.
- Finance Service: Escrow, commissions, payout calculations.
- Notification Service: Email, SMS, push, in-app.

