 4. Portal 2 – Vendor Center (Seller Center)

Accessible at `seller.yourdomain.com`, isolated by JWT with `role: vendor`.

 4.1 Multi-Step KYC Onboarding Pipeline

Statuses: `DRAFT` → `SUBMITTED` → `UNDER_REVIEW` → `APPROVED` / `REJECTED`.

Steps:
1. Business Information
   - Fields: business name, registered address (country, city), business type (dropdown: sole proprietor, LLC, etc.), industry category.
   - Upload business registration certificate (image/PDF).
   - OCR extraction for basic validation, but final approval manual.

2. Tax & Bank Details
   - TIN (Tax Identification Number) as per country.
   - VAT certificate if applicable.
   - Bank account for payouts: bank name, account number, account name.
   - Instant Bank Verification: System calls a bank API (e.g., Mono, Okra) to verify account name matches business name. On mismatch, flag for manual review.

3. Store Profile
   - Store name (unique per country), logo, banner.
   - Default shipping & return policies (choose from templates or custom text).
   - Customer service email/phone.

Backend: All documents stored in `kyc_documents`, vendor progress stored in `vendors.kyc_step`. On final submission, vendor status `UNDER_REVIEW` and admin is notified.

 4.2 Inventory & Product Management

 4.2.1 Product Creation with Variations
- Vendor creates base product (name, description, brand, category, images).
- Defines variation types (e.g., Size, Color) and values.
- System generates all combinations (SKU variations). For each:
  - SKU code (auto or manual), barcode (optional), price, sale price, weight (kg), dimensions (LxWxH cm), images specific to variation, quantity.
- Bulk Upload: Download CSV template, fill, upload. Validation same as form.

 4.2.2 Inventory Tracking
Two types:
- Jumia Express (FBJ): Vendor sees stock in Jumia warehouses per SKU. Can request to send more stock (inbound request). Dashboard shows available qty, reserved, inbound.
- Dropship: Vendor manages their own inventory. They update `vendor_inventory` with available qty. On order, system decrements this.

Low-Stock Alerts:
- Each SKU has `low_stock_threshold` (default 5).
- Cron job (every 30 min) checks `product_inventory.available_qty <= threshold` for Express; `vendor_inventory.available_qty <= threshold` for dropship.
- Generates notification (bell icon + email) to vendor.

 4.3 Order Fulfillment Dashboard (Dropship Focus)

When an order contains a dropship item, a `vendor_order` is created.

Dashboard View: List of orders to fulfill, filterable by status.

Statuses & Actions:
- `AWAITING_ACCEPTANCE`: Vendor has SLA deadline (`accept_deadline = order.paid_time + 2 hours`). They must click Accept. If not accepted in time, auto-cancellation triggered (see finance).
- `ACCEPTED`: Vendor must package and ship. Deadline `ship_deadline`. They can Print Shipping Label & Invoice (system generates PDF with barcode, customer address, hub drop-off address). Once packed, they either hand to carrier or drop at Jumia hub.
- At drop-off: Hub staff scans barcode → system updates status to `SHIPPED`, records tracking number. If vendor self-ships, they manually enter tracking and mark `SHIPPED`.
- After that, status flows normally (`IN_TRANSIT`, etc.).

Financial Info: Per order, vendor sees estimated earnings (item price - commission estimate).

 4.4 Returns & Disputes Management
- List of return requests from customers, with reason codes.
- Vendor can accept/refuse within 48h. If refused, escalated to admin.
- Returned item tracking for Express items.

 4.5 Performance & Reports
- Dashboard analytics: sales, returns rate, SLA compliance rate, customer feedback.
- Financial reports: pending withdrawals, settlement history.

