 8. Implementation Phases (From MVP to Enterprise)

The entire spec above is massive. Build incrementally:

Phase 1 – MVP (3 months):
- Single country, single warehouse (or dropship only), manual flat-rate shipping.
- Basic storefront, vendor registration (manual approval), simple order email for fulfillment.
- Payment integration (card), immediate wallet credit (no escrow), manual vendor payout.
- Admin: product approval, order view.

Phase 2 – Foundation (6 months):
- Multi-variation products, dynamic shipping zones, buyer address book.
- Basic escrow (manual release after return window), automated commission deduction.
- KYC automation (bank verification), vendor order acceptance flow with SLA.
- Automated refunds on cancel, low-stock alerts.

Phase 3 – Scale (12 months):
- Jumia Express warehouse, inbound/outbound, inventory reservation for flash sales.
- Full escrow cron, 7-day window, automated weekly payouts.
- Hub drop-off network, carrier tracking integration.
- Admin: commission config, reconciliation tools.

Phase 4 – Enterprise (Year 2+):
- Multi-country, multi-currency, cross-border shipping.
- Advanced WMS, RFQ for carriers, machine learning fraud detection.
- Advertising platform, seller financing.

